    <p><strong>Setting up a café in India in 2026 requires equipment investment ranging from ₹10 lakh for a small neighbourhood café to ₹60 lakh or more for a premium specialty coffee concept.</strong> The gap between success and failure often comes down to buying the right equipment — not the most expensive, not the cheapest, but the right fit for your menu, your volume, and your brand. This guide covers every category of equipment you need to open a café in India, with realistic prices sourced from Indian suppliers and honest advice on where to spend and where to save.</p>

