    <h2>1. Espresso Machines: The Heart of Your Café</h2>
    <p>Your espresso machine is the single most important investment in a coffee-focused café. It determines the quality of every espresso-based drink you serve — from a simple cappuccino to a complex single-origin cortado. Don't underestimate this purchase, but also don't overbuy for a menu and volume that doesn't justify it.</p>
    <p>Espresso machines are categorised by their group heads — each group head can pull one shot at a time. A 1-group machine serves roughly 50–100 cups per day before becoming a bottleneck. A 2-group machine handles 100–300 cups. A 3-group machine is needed for 300+ cups daily or for busy peak hours where multiple baristas work simultaneously.</p>

