    <h2>2. Coffee Grinders: Don't Cheap Out Here</h2>
    <p>If there is one area where café owners consistently make the mistake of under-investing, it's the grinder. A mediocre grinder will undermine even the best espresso machine. Fresh, consistent grind size is the foundation of good espresso — stale pre-ground coffee or an inconsistent grind produces sour, bitter, or flat shots regardless of how expensive your machine is.</p>
    <p>The rule in specialty coffee: your grinder should cost roughly as much as your espresso machine. That's not always practical, but it signals how important grinder quality is.</p>

    <h3>Coffee Grinder Prices in India 2026</h3>
