    <h2>4. Commercial Blenders: Smoothies, Frappes, and Cold Beverages</h2>
    <p>A good commercial blender is essential for any café serving cold beverages — frappes, smoothies, milkshakes, or cold coffee drinks. Consumer-grade blenders will burn out in weeks under café volume. Invest in a proper commercial unit from the start.</p>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Type</th><th>Price Range (INR)</th><th>Best For</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Entry commercial (Oster, Hamilton Beach)</td><td>₹8,000 – ₹20,000</td><td>Low volume, 20–40 drinks/day</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Mid-range commercial (Waring, Vitamix Drink Machine)</td><td>₹20,000 – ₹45,000</td><td>Medium volume, 40–100 drinks/day</td></tr>
        <tr><td>High-performance commercial (Vitamix Vita-Prep, Blendtec)</td><td>₹45,000 – ₹80,000</td><td>High volume, smoothie bar, 100+ drinks/day</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Batch blender (1.5–4L jug, Vitamix XL)</td><td>₹55,000 – ₹1,20,000</td><td>Bulk blending, cold brew, large batches</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p><strong>Pro tip:</strong> Buy a sound enclosure (sound dome) for your commercial blender. The noise from high-power blenders is jarring in a café environment and affects customer experience. Most premium blenders have matching enclosures available.</p>
    <p>For a café with a serious cold beverage menu, budget ₹35,000–₹60,000 for a Vitamix or Blendtec commercial unit. It will outlast three cheap blenders and your baristas will thank you.</p>

    <h2>5. POS Systems: Running Your Café Like a Business</h2>
    <p>A good POS system is the command centre of your café operations. Beyond processing payments, it tracks inventory, generates sales reports, manages your menu, and — increasingly — integrates with delivery platforms like Swiggy and Zomato. Don't run a café on a paper register in 2026.</p>

