    <h3>Popular POS Software for Indian Cafés</h3>
    <p><strong>Petpooja:</strong> India's most popular restaurant POS. Affordable, feature-rich, integrates with Swiggy and Zomato. ₹9,999–₹24,999 per year. Excellent for independent cafés.</p>
    <p><strong>UrbanPiper:</strong> Strong aggregator integration (Swiggy, Zomato, Dunzo). Better for cafés with heavy delivery focus. Monthly pricing varies.</p>
    <p><strong>LightSpeed:</strong> Popular with premium cafés, good inventory management, strong analytics. More expensive at ₹3,000–₹5,000/month.</p>
    <p><strong>Square:</strong> Easy to set up, good for small cafés. Limited India-specific features but reliable hardware.</p>
    <p><strong>Zoho POS:</strong> Part of Zoho ecosystem. Good integration with Zoho Books for accounting. Popular with cafés already using Zoho.</p>

    <h2>6. Furniture & Fixtures: Creating the Café Experience</h2>
    <p>Furniture is one of the highest-variable-cost categories in café setup. A basic neighbourhood café can be furnished for ₹1.5 lakh. A premium specialty coffee concept might spend ₹12–15 lakh on custom furniture alone. The right answer depends on your brand positioning and target customer.</p>

